Have you had friendships end? 
Let me tell you a little story.....

 I met Jennifer 22 years ago.  She worked at the bridal shop that had been a part of my life since I was 12.  Our friendship became stronger every year.  Marriage. Babies. Life's struggles and victories. She's the first person who said "YES" to building a YL business with me. I've watched her build her empire. She watched me build mine. Then one day..... the friendship ended.

Over. Done. Gone.

It was the worst emotional pain, aside from my father's death,  that I had ever experienced. 

 Neither one of us knew why, or how, or what was the reason other than "space was needed." 

And so I was met with 4 years of solitude. 
Four. 

And I fought it hard for two of those years.  I begged for answers,  I cried for the loss,  I hated the confusion, and I slipped into a horrible self-worth, destructive habits,  and a dark depression. 

As the solitude became the norm,  it became more palatable, and the past slipped into.... the past.  And I, focused on the future.  I studied mindset,  I locked into coaching with Bob Proctor, I turned inward and to Source and I discovered the pure BLISS of "F L O W" and the absolutely marvelous life it leads you to. 

Growth. Awareness. SELF.

What we BOTH realize now is that..... the solitude had to take place. The hurt, the confusion,  the anger, the sadness.... it all had to take place. 

The only way to rebuild yourself is to be torn down first.  In the process,  you discover who you are,  what you want,  and all that you are truly capable of. 

The best way to hear yourself think is in a quiet room by yourself... Solitude.  A block of time where all noise and distraction from the outside is removed. You are left with yourself and only your thoughts. 
LET relationships evolve.  LET growth happen.  LET yourself trust the process. What moves in to fill that space is  powerful and profound. HOLD SPACE for the good you desire. 

8 years ago we were only a fraction of the women we were created to be.  We came back into this friendship fiercely strong with an indescribable bond. 

Growth is a journey. Trust the process

REACT vs RESPOND 
...................................
Reaction comes from emotion, and response comes from intellect.  When we are quick to react,  to a situation we pull from what first comes to the surface which is personal feeling.  The situation may even feel intense and you might find yourself unable to take full control over your emotions whether that be anger or sadness.  The unfortunate part of reaction is that any valid or purposeful intention you may have had,  is diminished or even lost. 
In order to respond,  it requires a moment to go into the recesses of your memory,  and be intentional.  It gives you the ability to recall fact,  and find words best suited.  The result is clear,  concise communication that honors keeping the main thing, the main thing. 

When I'm headed into a conversation that may present conflict or confrontation I keep a small note card with me that simply says, "Everything just is.  REACT vs RESPOND.  Keep the main thing,  the main thing." The moment I feel the conversation becoming intense or heavy,  I make the conscious decision to honor the main thing,  and respond.  The moment information is presented that makes me feel frustrated,  fearful,  or angry I remind myself that everything is neutral. It is what it is. I have the power to give it direction to fear,  or faith. 

Pause and remind yourself that taking a moment so that you'll be able to respond and be intentional with your words,  truly is a power held in reserve that far too few realize. This will absolutely give you an advantage to win the day. 🥂
